cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on communication in automotive networks and proposes a middleware solution for QoS aware communication. 
2. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the use of a service-oriented architecture and middleware for software components in modern cars. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a protocol for dynamic QoS negotiation and a multi-protocol stack for communication in future cars, which involves distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the need for QoS agreements in time-sensitive network functions in cars, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve the use of algorithms and data structures for the implementation of the proposed middleware solution.
